				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hi Dan,
<br />

<br />
thanks for asking.
<br />

<br />
Strictly speaking, Textual Confirmation is under GPL license, just like phpBB itself. Therefore, you have a lot of liberty. But the kosher way for me for phpBB mass-hosting is:
<br />

<br />
One license per each 1000 users. If you have 2000 users, you need to purchase 2 licenses. If you have 10000 users, you need to purchase 10 licenses. Etc. It's assumed that you install TC to all users.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Since your standard license allows &quot;running on any number of computers&quot; I am sure that I could simply buy one copy and get it to run on many sites</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Not exactly. Actually, a license key is bound to the site name.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">As a side note, I also often run scripts that auto-install scripts like this onto my user boards (a little bit BOFH, but I do what is necessary).
